Text.SourceString: I really like the home office you set up for me. It even has my own sewing machine.
Text.LocalizedString: I really like the home office you set up for me. It even has my own sewing machine.

Text.SourceString: I put together a little something for you this morning, darling... A homemade breakfast. I hope you enjoy it.
Text.LocalizedString: I put together a little something for you this morning, darling... A homemade breakfast. I hope you enjoy it.

Text.SourceString: You know, dear, when I first started baking, I dreamed of sweet moments like these. Just you, me, and a home filled with the smell of fresh cookies.
Text.LocalizedString: You know, dear, when I first started baking, I dreamed of sweet moments like these. Just you, me, and a home filled with the smell of fresh cookies.

Text.SourceString: Sometimes I dream about us visiting exotic places together, <PlayerName>$Player</>.//But for now, being by your side in our cozy home is all the adventure I need.
Text.LocalizedString: Sometimes I dream about us visiting exotic places together, <PlayerName>$Player</>.//But for now, being by your side in our cozy home is all the adventure I need.

Text.SourceString: It's a beautiful day to go  around town, darling.//I think I might do that later.
Text.LocalizedString: It's a beautiful day to go  around town, darling.//I think I might do that later.

Text.SourceString: Every time I listen to music, I imagine us slow dancing in our kitchen.//Sounds silly, I know, but it makes me happy.
Text.LocalizedString: Every time I listen to music, I imagine us slow dancing in our kitchen.//Sounds silly, I know, but it makes me happy.

Text.SourceString: Remember how I always wanted to save up and see the world?//<portrait=happy>I realized that my world is right here, with you, in our lovely little home.
Text.LocalizedString: Remember how I always wanted to save up and see the world?//<portrait=happy>I realized that my world is right here, with you, in our lovely little home.

Text.SourceString: Hey <PlayerName>$Player</>... I love you.
Text.LocalizedString: Hey <PlayerName>$Player</>... I love you.

Text.SourceString: Did you have a good day today, <PlayerName>$Player</>? Tell me about it! I wanna hear it all.
Text.LocalizedString: Did you have a good day today, <PlayerName>$Player</>? Tell me about it! I wanna hear it all.

Text.SourceString: I spotted the cutest yellow bird just outside our window this morning.//I didn't snap a photo though, didn't want to scare it off.
Text.LocalizedString: I spotted the cutest yellow bird just outside our window this morning.//I didn't snap a photo though, didn't want to scare it off.

Text.SourceString: Oh, I've swapped out our sheets today. Fresh linens!
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, I've swapped out our sheets today. Fresh linens!

Text.SourceString: What do you think about a cozy evening in, baking cookies and just watching TV?
Text.LocalizedString: What do you think about a cozy evening in, baking cookies and just watching TV?

Text.SourceString: I love sprinkling a bit of sea salt on my cookies. It gives them that unexpected kick.
Text.LocalizedString: I love sprinkling a bit of sea salt on my cookies. It gives them that unexpected kick.

Text.SourceString: Good morning! How's your sleep?
Text.LocalizedString: Good morning! How's your sleep?

Text.SourceString: You're looking extra cute today, <PlayerName>$Player</>.
Text.LocalizedString: You're looking extra cute today, <PlayerName>$Player</>.

Text.SourceString: I'm so lucky to have you, <PlayerName>$Player</>.
Text.LocalizedString: I'm so lucky to have you, <PlayerName>$Player</>.

Text.SourceString: You're so good to me.
Text.LocalizedString: You're so good to me.

Text.SourceString: I know it's only Monday, but I hope you have a great week ahead, okay?
Text.LocalizedString: I know it's only Monday, but I hope you have a great week ahead, okay?

Text.SourceString: Please don't work so hard. I don't want you to get sick.
Text.LocalizedString: Please don't work so hard. I don't want you to get sick.

Text.SourceString: I remember those days at the inn, living with <NpcName>Macy</>, <NpcName>Raj</>, the twins, and little <NpcName>Valentina</>.//<portrait=normal>It was always buzzing with energy and love.
Text.LocalizedString: I remember those days at the inn, living with <NpcName>Macy</>, <NpcName>Raj</>, the twins, and little <NpcName>Valentina</>.//<portrait=normal>It was always buzzing with energy and love.

Text.SourceString: I miss waking up to <NpcName>Raj</>'s fresh coffee aromas sometimes.//They would brew coffee in their room and the aroma would fill up the whole second floor!
Text.LocalizedString: I miss waking up to <NpcName>Raj</>'s fresh coffee aromas sometimes.//They would brew coffee in their room and the aroma would fill up the whole second floor!

Text.SourceString: The twins always managed to keep the inn running smoothly.//It's remarkable, considering how many pies they have their fingers in!
Text.LocalizedString: The twins always managed to keep the inn running smoothly.//It's remarkable, considering how many pies they have their fingers in!

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Valentina</> is such a sweetie. She used to spend the weekend with <NpcName>Rafael</>, painting, playing at the beach... Oh!//<portrait=happy>She would come running back to the inn, leaving sand all over the floor. Ha ha!
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Valentina</> is such a sweetie. She used to spend the weekend with <NpcName>Rafael</>, painting, playing at the beach... Oh!//<portrait=happy>She would come running back to the inn, leaving sand all over the floor. Ha ha!

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Betty</> was telling me about how happy she is to see her children get along with each other.//<portrait=normal>It's good to see her happy.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Betty</> was telling me about how happy she is to see her children get along with each other.//<portrait=normal>It's good to see her happy.

Text.SourceString: Every time I visit <NpcName>Betty</>, I always eat a bucket full of chips. I can't help it.//<portrait=blushing>They're just too good!
Text.LocalizedString: Every time I visit <NpcName>Betty</>, I always eat a bucket full of chips. I can't help it.//<portrait=blushing>They're just too good!

Text.SourceString: Baking is nice, but sometimes I just want to stay at home with you.//<portrait=concerned>I guess I'm having one of those lazy days, darling.
Text.LocalizedString: Baking is nice, but sometimes I just want to stay at home with you.//<portrait=concerned>I guess I'm having one of those lazy days, darling.

Text.SourceString: My fingers are tired from kneading all that dough yesterday.
Text.LocalizedString: My fingers are tired from kneading all that dough yesterday.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Sam</> and <NpcName>Emily</> are great people. It's too bad that...well, you know...//<portrait=annoyed>It's too bad they can't have something they really want...a baby.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Sam</> and <NpcName>Emily</> are great people. It's too bad that...well, you know...//<portrait=annoyed>It's too bad they can't have something they really want...a baby.

Text.SourceString: If anyone deserves to be parents, it's them.
Text.LocalizedString: If anyone deserves to be parents, it's them.

Text.SourceString: What should we bring to the potluck tomorrow, dear?//What about some fresh eggs?
Text.LocalizedString: What should we bring to the potluck tomorrow, dear?//What about some fresh eggs?

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Raj</> sells expensive coffee. I don't know how a lot of people can afford it.//<portrait=annoyed>Every time I walk past, their coffee shop is always busy...
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Raj</> sells expensive coffee. I don't know how a lot of people can afford it.//<portrait=annoyed>Every time I walk past, their coffee shop is always busy...

Text.SourceString: I should bake some mooncakes for the festival. It would help <NpcName>Betty</> out.
Text.LocalizedString: I should bake some mooncakes for the festival. It would help <NpcName>Betty</> out.

Text.SourceString: Maybe I'll just go there and offer an extra hand.
Text.LocalizedString: Maybe I'll just go there and offer an extra hand.

Text.SourceString: How's farming today, dear?
Text.LocalizedString: How's farming today, dear?

Text.SourceString: Can we chill in bed after this? I don't feel like watching TV.//I just want to lie down and cuddle.
Text.LocalizedString: Can we chill in bed after this? I don't feel like watching TV.//I just want to lie down and cuddle.

Text.SourceString: I saw the cutest chipmunk today, reminds me of you.
Text.LocalizedString: I saw the cutest chipmunk today, reminds me of you.

Text.SourceString: I love you, <PlayerName>$Player</>.
Text.LocalizedString: I love you, <PlayerName>$Player</>.

Text.SourceString: Thank you, <PlayerName>$Player</>, for being such a great provider.
Text.LocalizedString: Thank you, <PlayerName>$Player</>, for being such a great provider.

Text.SourceString: I feel safe when you're around.
Text.LocalizedString: I feel safe when you're around.

Text.SourceString: I thought you should know that.
Text.LocalizedString: I thought you should know that.

Text.SourceString: Oh darling, you smell amazing. I love it.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh darling, you smell amazing. I love it.

Text.SourceString: Living at the inn was nice. It was like living in a small town.//But here, on this farm with you... it's different. It's so peaceful.
Text.LocalizedString: Living at the inn was nice. It was like living in a small town.//But here, on this farm with you... it's different. It's so peaceful.

Text.SourceString: I have to clean up the whole second floor. Dust everywhere!//Our house is a huge mess!
Text.LocalizedString: I have to clean up the whole second floor. Dust everywhere!//Our house is a huge mess!

Text.SourceString: Our house... That's a phrase I've dreamed of for so long.//<portrait=blushing>It's so delightful to finally say it!
Text.LocalizedString: Our house... That's a phrase I've dreamed of for so long.//<portrait=blushing>It's so delightful to finally say it!

Text.SourceString: Did you know you were snoring last night? It woke me up at midnight.//<portrait=annoyed>You must've been exhausted, darling.
Text.LocalizedString: Did you know you were snoring last night? It woke me up at midnight.//<portrait=annoyed>You must've been exhausted, darling.

Text.SourceString: Poor thing. It mustve been the heat!
Text.LocalizedString: Poor thing. It mustve been the heat!

Text.SourceString: I feel so awful for stray animals.//<portrait=sad>I wish we could build them little houses in the woods.
Text.LocalizedString: I feel so awful for stray animals.//<portrait=sad>I wish we could build them little houses in the woods.

Text.SourceString: Hmm. Yeah, there are plenty of trees and rocks for them to take shelter under.//<portrait=sad>You’re right.//But still.
Text.LocalizedString: Hmm. Yeah, there are plenty of trees and rocks for them to take shelter under.//<portrait=sad>You’re right.//But still.

Text.SourceString: I love the lake in Winter, when everything is still and frozen.//It looks so clean and pretty.//Mesmerizing to look at.
Text.LocalizedString: I love the lake in Winter, when everything is still and frozen.//It looks so clean and pretty.//Mesmerizing to look at.

Text.SourceString: I opened our window this morning, and the mist woke me right up.
Text.LocalizedString: I opened our window this morning, and the mist woke me right up.

Text.SourceString: I just love your style, darling! Oh and <NpcName>Leah</>! You and she have great style.//<portrait=normal>I like to pay attention to people’s outfits. You know, for inspiration.
Text.LocalizedString: I just love your style, darling! Oh and <NpcName>Leah</>! You and she have great style.//<portrait=normal>I like to pay attention to people’s outfits. You know, for inspiration.

Text.SourceString: The red velvet cake at Fishensips is so yum!//I don’t know what I’d do if <NpcName>Frank</> stopped making it.
Text.LocalizedString: The red velvet cake at Fishensips is so yum!//I don’t know what I’d do if <NpcName>Frank</> stopped making it.

Text.SourceString: I’ve tried copying <NpcName>Frank’s</> recipe many times, but mine is never as good.
Text.LocalizedString: I’ve tried copying <NpcName>Frank’s</> recipe many times, but mine is never as good.

Text.SourceString: For some reason, I always crave red velvet cake on Fridays.//<portrait=normal>You know, maybe it’s like a celebration. Maybe.//<portrait=annoyed>In my mind, red velvet cake marks the end of the week.//I don’t know.
Text.LocalizedString: For some reason, I always crave red velvet cake on Fridays.//<portrait=normal>You know, maybe it’s like a celebration. Maybe.//<portrait=annoyed>In my mind, red velvet cake marks the end of the week.//I don’t know.

Text.SourceString: Hmm. Do you think there’s, like, a green velvet cake?//<portrait=happy>Should I try making one with lettuce?//<portrait=annoyed>Doesn’t sound very appealing, to be honest.
Text.LocalizedString: Hmm. Do you think there’s, like, a green velvet cake?//<portrait=happy>Should I try making one with lettuce?//<portrait=annoyed>Doesn’t sound very appealing, to be honest.

Text.SourceString: I had a slice of bread for a quick breakfast this morning.//And some fruit from the kitchen.
Text.LocalizedString: I had a slice of bread for a quick breakfast this morning.//And some fruit from the kitchen.

Text.SourceString: Well, if I had to choose, cookies are probably my best baked goods.//I make them all the time, so I think I might have maxed out my cookie-baking skills.
Text.LocalizedString: Well, if I had to choose, cookies are probably my best baked goods.//I make them all the time, so I think I might have maxed out my cookie-baking skills.

Text.SourceString: Practice does make perfect. I owe it to all those hours I spent working at Sam's, making cookies.
Text.LocalizedString: Practice does make perfect. I owe it to all those hours I spent working at Sam's, making cookies.

Text.SourceString: I often find wasabi growing by the lake this time of year.//<portrait=happy>Have you found any yet, darling?
Text.LocalizedString: I often find wasabi growing by the lake this time of year.//<portrait=happy>Have you found any yet, darling?

Text.SourceString: The beach is still a little cold.//Have you ever found anything pretty while diving?//<portrait=surprised>You have?
Text.LocalizedString: The beach is still a little cold.//Have you ever found anything pretty while diving?//<portrait=surprised>You have?

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Theo</> showed me a handful of jade a long time ago.//<portrait=happy>He told me he found it in an old treasure chest.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Theo</> showed me a handful of jade a long time ago.//<portrait=happy>He told me he found it in an old treasure chest.

Text.SourceString: With Summer right around the corner, it must be a busy time for you as a farmer, huh?
Text.LocalizedString: With Summer right around the corner, it must be a busy time for you as a farmer, huh?

Text.SourceString: Don't worry, darling. I'm here to help.
Text.LocalizedString: Don't worry, darling. I'm here to help.

Text.SourceString: Peonies are the prettiest flowers in the world, don’t you think?//<portrait=normal>Their blossoms are so big, and their colors are so vivid.
Text.LocalizedString: Peonies are the prettiest flowers in the world, don’t you think?//<portrait=normal>Their blossoms are so big, and their colors are so vivid.

Text.SourceString: Too bad they only bloom in the Spring.
Text.LocalizedString: Too bad they only bloom in the Spring.

Text.SourceString: The snow melts so fast.//It’s already gone, and Spring just started!
Text.LocalizedString: The snow melts so fast.//It’s already gone, and Spring just started!

Text.SourceString: I can’t wait for the Cherry Blossom Festival. It’ll be so much fun.//I might try my luck with balap karung this year. I don’t know! Maybeeeee!
Text.LocalizedString: I can’t wait for the Cherry Blossom Festival. It’ll be so much fun.//I might try my luck with balap karung this year. I don’t know! Maybeeeee!

Text.SourceString: Are we going to plant flowers on our farm?
Text.LocalizedString: Are we going to plant flowers on our farm?

Text.SourceString: Coral Island is just so beautiful in the Spring. I’m glad we live here.
Text.LocalizedString: Coral Island is just so beautiful in the Spring. I’m glad we live here.

Text.SourceString: I prefer Spring to Summer. But if we’re talking favorites, it would definitely be Winter.//It’s more bearable working in front of the oven in Winter.
Text.LocalizedString: I prefer Spring to Summer. But if we’re talking favorites, it would definitely be Winter.//It’s more bearable working in front of the oven in Winter.

Text.SourceString: What do you think would be the perfect baked good for Spring?//<portrait=happy>For me, probably something colorful like a fruit tart. So yum!
Text.LocalizedString: What do you think would be the perfect baked good for Spring?//<portrait=happy>For me, probably something colorful like a fruit tart. So yum!

Text.SourceString: The inn didn't have a good air conditioner.//It sort of turned on and off by itself sometimes. My old room could get pretty hot.
Text.LocalizedString: The inn didn't have a good air conditioner.//It sort of turned on and off by itself sometimes. My old room could get pretty hot.

Text.SourceString: I grew up with this kind of weather, hot and humid basically all year long.//So yeah, I’m used to it, but working in front of the oven in this weather is still…something.
Text.LocalizedString: I grew up with this kind of weather, hot and humid basically all year long.//So yeah, I’m used to it, but working in front of the oven in this weather is still…something.

Text.SourceString: So glad I picked this blouse today.//It’s nice and breezy!
Text.LocalizedString: So glad I picked this blouse today.//It’s nice and breezy!

Text.SourceString: The Beach Cleanup Festival happens right in front of the inn.//I used to wake up to people getting the festival ready.
Text.LocalizedString: The Beach Cleanup Festival happens right in front of the inn.//I used to wake up to people getting the festival ready.

Text.SourceString: It’s not bad living at the inn, on the second floor especially. Yeah, it does get really hot in Summer because of the broken air conditioner.//<portrait=normal>But after sunset, you open the window, and the salty breeze is just divine!
Text.LocalizedString: It’s not bad living at the inn, on the second floor especially. Yeah, it does get really hot in Summer because of the broken air conditioner.//<portrait=normal>But after sunset, you open the window, and the salty breeze is just divine!

Text.SourceString: I might enter the swimming contest next week. It’ll be fun, even if I’m not a great swimmer. Especially compared to <NPCName>Sunny</>!//<portrait=surprised>He doesn’t move that fast when he’s walking!
Text.LocalizedString: I might enter the swimming contest next week. It’ll be fun, even if I’m not a great swimmer. Especially compared to <NPCName>Sunny</>!//<portrait=surprised>He doesn’t move that fast when he’s walking!

Text.SourceString: Have you seen those cute little white flowers growing everywhere?//What are those? I think they’re daisies.//Are they daisies, you think?
Text.LocalizedString: Have you seen those cute little white flowers growing everywhere?//What are those? I think they’re daisies.//Are they daisies, you think?

Text.SourceString: Isn’t this the best season for cookies and tea?
Text.LocalizedString: Isn’t this the best season for cookies and tea?

Text.SourceString: Fall is so pretty, isn’t it? Back home, the trees never looked like this.
Text.LocalizedString: Fall is so pretty, isn’t it? Back home, the trees never looked like this.

Text.SourceString: The Harvest Festival here is so cool.//It’s nothing like the one we had when I was growing up.
Text.LocalizedString: The Harvest Festival here is so cool.//It’s nothing like the one we had when I was growing up.

Text.SourceString: It is a bit chilly right now, but I much prefer it to the heat of Summer.
Text.LocalizedString: It is a bit chilly right now, but I much prefer it to the heat of Summer.

Text.SourceString: It’s getting colder, isn’t it? I guess it’s a sign Winter is just around the corner.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s getting colder, isn’t it? I guess it’s a sign Winter is just around the corner.

Text.SourceString: Fall is one of the reasons I decided to move here. It’s the most beautiful thing I’ve ever seen.//<portrait=happy>And who wouldn’t want to wake up to see that every day?
Text.LocalizedString: Fall is one of the reasons I decided to move here. It’s the most beautiful thing I’ve ever seen.//<portrait=happy>And who wouldn’t want to wake up to see that every day?

Text.SourceString: I want to bake some pumpkin pies. Might as well since pumpkins are in season, right?
Text.LocalizedString: I want to bake some pumpkin pies. Might as well since pumpkins are in season, right?

Text.SourceString: I hardly ever baked pumpkin pie until I moved here. I was missing out!
Text.LocalizedString: I hardly ever baked pumpkin pie until I moved here. I was missing out!

Text.SourceString: I love snow, you know. It’s so fascinating, the way it’s soft and fluffy but also cold and clumpy.//It feels magical.
Text.LocalizedString: I love snow, you know. It’s so fascinating, the way it’s soft and fluffy but also cold and clumpy.//It feels magical.

Text.SourceString: I don’t think I’ll ever get bored of snow. I didn’t grow up with it, so I always find it mesmerizing.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t think I’ll ever get bored of snow. I didn’t grow up with it, so I always find it mesmerizing.

Text.SourceString: Better make sure my heater works. The inn’s central heating isn’t warm enough for me.//<portrait=surprised>Oh, but don’t tell <NPCName>Suki</>! She can be scary sometimes.
Text.LocalizedString: Better make sure my heater works. The inn’s central heating isn’t warm enough for me.//<portrait=surprised>Oh, but don’t tell <NPCName>Suki</>! She can be scary sometimes.

Text.SourceString: These are the days when I’m super glad I’m a baker. I have my own personal heater at work!
Text.LocalizedString: These are the days when I’m super glad I’m a baker. I have my own personal heater at work!

Text.SourceString: You look all nice and cozy today.
Text.LocalizedString: You look all nice and cozy today.

Text.SourceString: I usually don’t notice how much heat the oven radiates until it’s Summer.//<PlayerName>$player</>, it’s really hot!
Text.LocalizedString: I usually don’t notice how much heat the oven radiates until it’s Summer.//<PlayerName>$player</>, it’s really hot!

Text.SourceString: Winter is the perfect time to slow down a little.//Reflect on the year and stuff.
Text.LocalizedString: Winter is the perfect time to slow down a little.//Reflect on the year and stuff.

Text.SourceString: I kind of want to play in the snow in the park with the kids. <NPCName>Valentina</> always looks like she’s having so much fun playing outside.
Text.LocalizedString: I kind of want to play in the snow in the park with the kids. <NPCName>Valentina</> always looks like she’s having so much fun playing outside.

Text.SourceString: Living by the sea isn’t as fun as it sounds.//Especially in Summer.
Text.LocalizedString: Living by the sea isn’t as fun as it sounds.//Especially in Summer.

Text.SourceString: I know, I know.//<portrait=concerned>I sound like a brat, but it gets so humid, my hair doubles in volume.
Text.LocalizedString: I know, I know.//<portrait=concerned>I sound like a brat, but it gets so humid, my hair doubles in volume.

Text.SourceString: When I have time, I’ll forage around the woodland for fresh Summer veggies and flowers.
Text.LocalizedString: When I have time, I’ll forage around the woodland for fresh Summer veggies and flowers.

Text.SourceString: The best thing is when I find jackfruit.//<portrait=normal>I always share some with <NpcName>Bree</>, the wine lady. She loves to make a fancy meal out of it.
Text.LocalizedString: The best thing is when I find jackfruit.//<portrait=normal>I always share some with <NpcName>Bree</>, the wine lady. She loves to make a fancy meal out of it.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Bree</> makes a delicious shredded jackfruit pie.//<portrait=happy>Oh, don’t worry! It’s vegan, in case you are.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Bree</> makes a delicious shredded jackfruit pie.//<portrait=happy>Oh, don’t worry! It’s vegan, in case you are.

Text.SourceString: Oh, almost forget to tell you.//<portrait=normal>Did you know you can find shallots around the lake this time of year?
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, almost forget to tell you.//<portrait=normal>Did you know you can find shallots around the lake this time of year?

Text.SourceString: My favorite festivals are the Animal Festival and the Harvest Festival!//I like the Cherry Blossom Festival potluck too. It’s just that it’s always so early in Spring. It’s still too cold to be outside all day.
Text.LocalizedString: My favorite festivals are the Animal Festival and the Harvest Festival!//I like the Cherry Blossom Festival potluck too. It’s just that it’s always so early in Spring. It’s still too cold to be outside all day.

Text.SourceString: I love Summer, but I’m ready for it to cool down a little.
Text.LocalizedString: I love Summer, but I’m ready for it to cool down a little.

Text.SourceString: I’m so ready for some green tea and cookie weather.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m so ready for some green tea and cookie weather.

Text.SourceString: The leaves were so crunchy when I walked to work this morning. They were satisfying to step on.
Text.LocalizedString: The leaves were so crunchy when I walked to work this morning. They were satisfying to step on.

Text.SourceString: Oh, come on! You’re telling me you’ve never gone out of your way to find a pile of crunchy leaves just to step on them?
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, come on! You’re telling me you’ve never gone out of your way to find a pile of crunchy leaves just to step on them?

Text.SourceString: The farm is so misty the mornings this time of year.//What a perfect way to start our day.
Text.LocalizedString: The farm is so misty the mornings this time of year.//What a perfect way to start our day.

Text.SourceString: I’m turning on our heater tonight. It’s starting to get too cold for me.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m turning on our heater tonight. It’s starting to get too cold for me.

Text.SourceString: I don’t eat out much. I don’t know. I guess the dishes I actually love, I can make myself.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t eat out much. I don’t know. I guess the dishes I actually love, I can make myself.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Frank</> and <NpcName>Betty</> still have the best red velvet cake in town, though.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Frank</> and <NpcName>Betty</> still have the best red velvet cake in town, though.

Text.SourceString: When the snow blankets the town like this, it’s hard to tell the buildings apart. Until you go inside, you don’t know whose house it really is.
Text.LocalizedString: When the snow blankets the town like this, it’s hard to tell the buildings apart. Until you go inside, you don’t know whose house it really is.

Text.SourceString: A beautiful analogy to remind us not to judge one another, I think.
Text.LocalizedString: A beautiful analogy to remind us not to judge one another, I think.

Text.SourceString: I always get all sappy in Winter. Argh…
Text.LocalizedString: I always get all sappy in Winter. Argh…

Text.SourceString: One day, I want to throw fancy parties like <NpcName>Bree’s</> annual dinner party. Ah, you know! With a dress code and an elaborate theme and stuff.
Text.LocalizedString: One day, I want to throw fancy parties like <NpcName>Bree’s</> annual dinner party. Ah, you know! With a dress code and an elaborate theme and stuff.

Text.SourceString: Oh yes! A party where we all can eat fancy food and sip fine drinks. Oh, and everybody has a great time. That would be fabulous.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh yes! A party where we all can eat fancy food and sip fine drinks. Oh, and everybody has a great time. That would be fabulous.

Text.SourceString: Be careful out there, dear. The path might be slippery.
Text.LocalizedString: Be careful out there, dear. The path might be slippery.

Text.SourceString: I’m not going to hike today. I’m afraid I might slip.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m not going to hike today. I’m afraid I might slip.

Text.SourceString: Oh my! Stop teasing.//Not a joke. I was being serious.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh my! Stop teasing.//Not a joke. I was being serious.

Text.SourceString: It’s nice and warm here.//Hmm…
Text.LocalizedString: It’s nice and warm here.//Hmm…

Text.SourceString: Why do rainy nights always make me feel sooooo melancholy…
Text.LocalizedString: Why do rainy nights always make me feel sooooo melancholy…

Text.SourceString: *sighs*
Text.LocalizedString: *sighs*

Text.SourceString: *shivering* I need to stand near the fireplace.//<portrait=sad>I’m not built for this type of weather.
Text.LocalizedString: *shivering* I need to stand near the fireplace.//<portrait=sad>I’m not built for this type of weather.

Text.SourceString: Today was a long day! With the snow and all.//<portrait=sad>Good gosh.
Text.LocalizedString: Today was a long day! With the snow and all.//<portrait=sad>Good gosh.

Text.SourceString: Wow. In snow like this, you can really see everyone’s footprints!//Which ones are yours?
Text.LocalizedString: Wow. In snow like this, you can really see everyone’s footprints!//Which ones are yours?

Text.SourceString: It’s either fluffy or slippery this time of year. You really have to be careful going around, darling.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s either fluffy or slippery this time of year. You really have to be careful going around, darling.

Text.SourceString: Should we build a snowman today?//I mean, this is definitely the weather for it.//<portrait=happy>It could be fun.
Text.LocalizedString: Should we build a snowman today?//I mean, this is definitely the weather for it.//<portrait=happy>It could be fun.

Text.SourceString: The baked goods here are made fresh every day, darling.//Don’t you worry, <PlayerName>$player</>. I can vouch for that because I bake everything myself.
Text.LocalizedString: The baked goods here are made fresh every day, darling.//Don’t you worry, <PlayerName>$player</>. I can vouch for that because I bake everything myself.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Sam</> always insists we use only the best ingredients.//He believes you can taste quality, and I kind of agree with him on that.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Sam</> always insists we use only the best ingredients.//He believes you can taste quality, and I kind of agree with him on that.

Text.SourceString: Hey darling! It's nice to see you here.//<portrait=happy>Do you miss me?
Text.LocalizedString: Hey darling! It's nice to see you here.//<portrait=happy>Do you miss me?

Text.SourceString: I really wanna kiss you, but we can't kiss here!//My boss is right there!
Text.LocalizedString: I really wanna kiss you, but we can't kiss here!//My boss is right there!

Text.SourceString: I made fruit tarts today.//I used fresh blueberries, but you can use literally any fruit.
Text.LocalizedString: I made fruit tarts today.//I used fresh blueberries, but you can use literally any fruit.

Text.SourceString: Starlet is such a beautiful town, and I think people truly care about each other here.//<portrait=happy>I can feel it.
Text.LocalizedString: Starlet is such a beautiful town, and I think people truly care about each other here.//<portrait=happy>I can feel it.

Text.SourceString: Growing up, my parents told me if you have people who care about you, you have a good life.//<portrait=blushing>Now that I have you, I see what they meant.
Text.LocalizedString: Growing up, my parents told me if you have people who care about you, you have a good life.//<portrait=blushing>Now that I have you, I see what they meant.

Text.SourceString: The smell of fresh baked goods can really liven up a place.
Text.LocalizedString: The smell of fresh baked goods can really liven up a place.

Text.SourceString: I like to take inspiration from the beach sometimes.//<portrait=happy>The shells, the sea… So much material.
Text.LocalizedString: I like to take inspiration from the beach sometimes.//<portrait=happy>The shells, the sea… So much material.

Text.SourceString: Isn’t the lake beautiful in Winter?//So placid. So still.
Text.LocalizedString: Isn’t the lake beautiful in Winter?//So placid. So still.

Text.SourceString: Winter makes everything look so different, doesn’t it?
Text.LocalizedString: Winter makes everything look so different, doesn’t it?

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Betty</> and I have this little ritual.//<portrait=normal>Every Sunday, one of us bakes a little cake, and we share it!
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Betty</> and I have this little ritual.//<portrait=normal>Every Sunday, one of us bakes a little cake, and we share it!

Text.SourceString: I totally love our time together, but I also think it's kinda important for us to do stuff on our own sometimes.
Text.LocalizedString: I totally love our time together, but I also think it's kinda important for us to do stuff on our own sometimes.

Text.SourceString: I love it here.//<portrait=normal>It’s so peaceful but so full of life too.
Text.LocalizedString: I love it here.//<portrait=normal>It’s so peaceful but so full of life too.

Text.SourceString: I love the way Sam’s smells. Most stores smell weird, but we keep this place spick-and-span!
Text.LocalizedString: I love the way Sam’s smells. Most stores smell weird, but we keep this place spick-and-span!

Text.SourceString: It’s a shame to stay inside all day when the weather’s like this.//<portrait=concerned>But I’m so busy, what choice do I have?
Text.LocalizedString: It’s a shame to stay inside all day when the weather’s like this.//<portrait=concerned>But I’m so busy, what choice do I have?

Text.SourceString: The weather report said it would rain all day.//<portrait=concerned>And it was right! It’s still going out there.
Text.LocalizedString: The weather report said it would rain all day.//<portrait=concerned>And it was right! It’s still going out there.

Text.SourceString: I love the rain. It casts everything in a new light, and it smells great.
Text.LocalizedString: I love the rain. It casts everything in a new light, and it smells great.

Text.SourceString: It’s a shame to stay inside all day when the weather’s like this.//<portrait=concerned>But I’m so busy, what choice do I have?
Text.LocalizedString: It’s a shame to stay inside all day when the weather’s like this.//<portrait=concerned>But I’m so busy, what choice do I have?

Text.SourceString: The weather report said it would rain all day.//<portrait=concerned>And it was right! It’s still going out there.
Text.LocalizedString: The weather report said it would rain all day.//<portrait=concerned>And it was right! It’s still going out there.

Text.SourceString: I love the rain. It casts everything in a new light, and it smells great.
Text.LocalizedString: I love the rain. It casts everything in a new light, and it smells great.

Text.SourceString: Baking is a science as much as it is an art. It takes a lot of technical expertise to make the perfect bread.
Text.LocalizedString: Baking is a science as much as it is an art. It takes a lot of technical expertise to make the perfect bread.

Text.SourceString: But don’t let that discourage you!//Learning from your mistakes is half the fun.
Text.LocalizedString: But don’t let that discourage you!//Learning from your mistakes is half the fun.

Text.SourceString: I like being this close to you... You smell amazing.
Text.LocalizedString: I like being this close to you... You smell amazing.

Text.SourceString: This shirt is my own creation. I worked on the batik myself.//Borrowed the tools in the community center, got some dye online. That’s it.
Text.LocalizedString: This shirt is my own creation. I worked on the batik myself.//Borrowed the tools in the community center, got some dye online. That’s it.

Text.SourceString: It took me a while to make it. But the pattern is pretty, don’t you think? All the work was worth it, in my book.
Text.LocalizedString: It took me a while to make it. But the pattern is pretty, don’t you think? All the work was worth it, in my book.

Text.SourceString: I got a couple of my bracelets from my childhood friends.//They probably cost next to nothing, but they’re very special to me.
Text.LocalizedString: I got a couple of my bracelets from my childhood friends.//They probably cost next to nothing, but they’re very special to me.

Text.SourceString: How’s your week so far?//<portrait=concerned>You must be pretty busy, huh?
Text.LocalizedString: How’s your week so far?//<portrait=concerned>You must be pretty busy, huh?

Text.SourceString: Maybe we could just relax and watch TV together one of these days.
Text.LocalizedString: Maybe we could just relax and watch TV together one of these days.

Text.SourceString: Wild fruits are great food source.//You can gather them around the lake and make pies or meals out of them.//<portrait=happy>That’s what I do. Saves me a ton of money.
Text.LocalizedString: Wild fruits are great food source.//You can gather them around the lake and make pies or meals out of them.//<portrait=happy>That’s what I do. Saves me a ton of money.

Text.SourceString: I don’t want to make this about me, but I really like talking to you, darling.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t want to make this about me, but I really like talking to you, darling.

Text.SourceString: You’re always so kind to me. I feel appreciated.
Text.LocalizedString: You’re always so kind to me. I feel appreciated.

Text.SourceString: Lots of our customers are looking for mooncakes.//I tell them we don’t sell them.<NpcName>Sam</> won’t budge. They cost too much to make.//Anyway, I tell them to try Fishensips.
Text.LocalizedString: Lots of our customers are looking for mooncakes.//I tell them we don’t sell them.<NpcName>Sam</> won’t budge. They cost too much to make.//Anyway, I tell them to try Fishensips.

Text.SourceString: Who knows? Maybe if enough people ask for them at Fishensips, <NpcName>Frank</> might start selling them.//<portrait=normal>I’d buy them!
Text.LocalizedString: Who knows? Maybe if enough people ask for them at Fishensips, <NpcName>Frank</> might start selling them.//<portrait=normal>I’d buy them!

Text.SourceString: I enjoy making clothes for myself, but I’m not sure about making clothes for a living.//Baking, yeah. I can do that every day, but <Italic>batiking</>? Hmm. Not sure.
Text.LocalizedString: I enjoy making clothes for myself, but I’m not sure about making clothes for a living.//Baking, yeah. I can do that every day, but <Italic>batiking</>? Hmm. Not sure.

Text.SourceString: Do you think I could sell these clothes?
Text.LocalizedString: Do you think I could sell these clothes?

Text.SourceString: I lost a hat a long time ago and found it by the park next to a snowman.//<portrait=sad>I wonder how it got there.
Text.LocalizedString: I lost a hat a long time ago and found it by the park next to a snowman.//<portrait=sad>I wonder how it got there.

Text.SourceString: I couldn’t wear it anymore. It got all soggy and lost its shape.//<portrait=sad>Went straight into the trash. What a waste.
Text.LocalizedString: I couldn’t wear it anymore. It got all soggy and lost its shape.//<portrait=sad>Went straight into the trash. What a waste.

Text.SourceString: I stayed up late last night...//I kept hearing scratching from the kitchen.
Text.LocalizedString: I stayed up late last night...//I kept hearing scratching from the kitchen.

Text.SourceString: I'm worried we might have rats.
Text.LocalizedString: I'm worried we might have rats.

Text.SourceString: I gave <NpcName>Macy</> a beanie that I sewed for her birthday in Spring, but I’ve never seen her wearing it.
Text.LocalizedString: I gave <NpcName>Macy</> a beanie that I sewed for her birthday in Spring, but I’ve never seen her wearing it.

Text.SourceString: She probably doesn’t like it. What do you think?//<portrait=concerned>Well, I guess you’re right. It’s still Summer. Maybe she’ll wear it when the weather cools off.
Text.LocalizedString: She probably doesn’t like it. What do you think?//<portrait=concerned>Well, I guess you’re right. It’s still Summer. Maybe she’ll wear it when the weather cools off.

Text.SourceString: I always give <NpcName>Macy</> beanies for her birthday.//<portrait=concerned>Do you think she has too many beanies already?//Should I make her something else next year?
Text.LocalizedString: I always give <NpcName>Macy</> beanies for her birthday.//<portrait=concerned>Do you think she has too many beanies already?//Should I make her something else next year?

Text.SourceString: I crocheted this scarf myself.//<portrait=happy>I got the yarn online. It was on sale.
Text.LocalizedString: I crocheted this scarf myself.//<portrait=happy>I got the yarn online. It was on sale.

Text.SourceString: We’re lucky the area in front of our farm doesn’t pile up with snow too much.
Text.LocalizedString: We’re lucky the area in front of our farm doesn’t pile up with snow too much.

Text.SourceString: Nice shirt!
Text.LocalizedString: Nice shirt!

Text.SourceString: I really like your outfit today. It’s so you, you know?
Text.LocalizedString: I really like your outfit today. It’s so you, you know?

Text.SourceString: Nice shirt!
Text.LocalizedString: Nice shirt!

Text.SourceString: I really like your outfit today. It’s so springy, you know?
Text.LocalizedString: I really like your outfit today. It’s so springy, you know?

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Betty’s</> always teasing me because I talk about you so much.//<portrait=blushing>What am I supposed to do, though?
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Betty’s</> always teasing me because I talk about you so much.//<portrait=blushing>What am I supposed to do, though?

Text.SourceString: When things get hard, I like to start a new project to unwind.//Creating takes my mind off things.
Text.LocalizedString: When things get hard, I like to start a new project to unwind.//Creating takes my mind off things.

Text.SourceString: But it’s not a good solution.//<portrait=sad>I end up with a lot of unfinished projects.//<portrait=annoyed>I like the starting out part. Following through isn’t my biggest strength.
Text.LocalizedString: But it’s not a good solution.//<portrait=sad>I end up with a lot of unfinished projects.//<portrait=annoyed>I like the starting out part. Following through isn’t my biggest strength.

Text.SourceString: I’d love to pick up some peonies for our room.//<portrait=concerned><NpcName>Ratih</> didn’t have any the last time I checked.//<NpcName>Ben</> might have some, but I don’t wanna go all the way there to check.
Text.LocalizedString: I’d love to pick up some peonies for our room.//<portrait=concerned><NpcName>Ratih</> didn’t have any the last time I checked.//<NpcName>Ben</> might have some, but I don’t wanna go all the way there to check.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Raj</> has their own coffee shop.//<portrait=happy>It’s pretty neat, I think. They always give me a discount too.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Raj</> has their own coffee shop.//<portrait=happy>It’s pretty neat, I think. They always give me a discount too.

Text.SourceString: It’s very kind of them, but honestly, I feel bad going there now.//I don’t want them to keep selling at a discount.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s very kind of them, but honestly, I feel bad going there now.//I don’t want them to keep selling at a discount.

Text.SourceString: Hopefully, <NpcName>Ratih</> has some orchids.//I’d love to buy some.
Text.LocalizedString: Hopefully, <NpcName>Ratih</> has some orchids.//I’d love to buy some.

Text.SourceString: I wonder if she’s at the dock today.//What day is this?
Text.LocalizedString: I wonder if she’s at the dock today.//What day is this?

Text.SourceString: I saw a couple of seals swimming earlier!
Text.LocalizedString: I saw a couple of seals swimming earlier!

Text.SourceString: It’s nice to see you relaxing, dear!
Text.LocalizedString: It’s nice to see you relaxing, dear!

Text.SourceString: Crowds don’t bother me.//<portrait=happy>I like them, actually.
Text.LocalizedString: Crowds don’t bother me.//<portrait=happy>I like them, actually.

Text.SourceString: You have sand on your cheeks.//<portrait=normal>How did it get there?
Text.LocalizedString: You have sand on your cheeks.//<portrait=normal>How did it get there?

Text.SourceString: It’s such a nice day I thought I’d spend it outside.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s such a nice day I thought I’d spend it outside.

Text.SourceString: Maybe I’ll fill up my water bottle with some iced tea later.//<portrait=happy>Hmm. Yeah, that sounds good!
Text.LocalizedString: Maybe I’ll fill up my water bottle with some iced tea later.//<portrait=happy>Hmm. Yeah, that sounds good!

Text.SourceString: I ran into <NpcName>Betty</> this morning.//She was gardening over at the monument park, the one in front of the laboratory.
Text.LocalizedString: I ran into <NpcName>Betty</> this morning.//She was gardening over at the monument park, the one in front of the laboratory.

Text.SourceString: They have a yoga class here on the weekend.//Right there, by those benches.
Text.LocalizedString: They have a yoga class here on the weekend.//Right there, by those benches.

Text.SourceString: I’m not big on yoga or working out in general, to be honest.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m not big on yoga or working out in general, to be honest.

Text.SourceString: I’ve seen <NpcName>Leah</> doing yoga here a couple of times. Sometimes at the beach too.//<portrait=happy>She always looks so graceful.//<portrait=normal>I love her hair. And her wardrobe! Her wardrobe is to die for.
Text.LocalizedString: I’ve seen <NpcName>Leah</> doing yoga here a couple of times. Sometimes at the beach too.//<portrait=happy>She always looks so graceful.//<portrait=normal>I love her hair. And her wardrobe! Her wardrobe is to die for.

Text.SourceString: I could never afford her style.//<portrait=happy>Maybe someday?
Text.LocalizedString: I could never afford her style.//<portrait=happy>Maybe someday?

Text.SourceString: I ran into the mayor the other day.//<portrait=surprised>He was wearing a cactus on his hat.//<portrait=normal>No, I’m not joking.
Text.LocalizedString: I ran into the mayor the other day.//<portrait=surprised>He was wearing a cactus on his hat.//<portrait=normal>No, I’m not joking.

Text.SourceString: The cactus had a little flower on top of it. Gosh! It was so adorable.
Text.LocalizedString: The cactus had a little flower on top of it. Gosh! It was so adorable.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Valentina</> and I made beanies last week.//She’s good at it. She even made extra for her grandparents.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Valentina</> and I made beanies last week.//She’s good at it. She even made extra for her grandparents.

Text.SourceString: I haven’t seen <NpcName>Valentina</> wearing her beanie yet.//<portrait=happy>Maybe she’ll wear it in Winter.
Text.LocalizedString: I haven’t seen <NpcName>Valentina</> wearing her beanie yet.//<portrait=happy>Maybe she’ll wear it in Winter.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Alice</> has a great collection of boots.//She told me I could borrow them if I’d like. But I don’t know.//<portrait=concerned>I don’t want to be a bother.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Alice</> has a great collection of boots.//She told me I could borrow them if I’d like. But I don’t know.//<portrait=concerned>I don’t want to be a bother.

Text.SourceString: <Italic>Brrrr.</> It’s so cold today!
Text.LocalizedString: <Italic>Brrrr.</> It’s so cold today!

Text.SourceString: Ever since I was little, I've dreamt about a day like yesterday, where I walked down the aisle to marry the love of my life.//It feels surreal that my childhood dreams have become a beautiful reality.
Text.LocalizedString: Ever since I was little, I've dreamt about a day like yesterday, where I walked down the aisle to marry the love of my life.//It feels surreal that my childhood dreams have become a beautiful reality.

Text.SourceString: We're married now, <PlayerName>$Player</>...I'm your wife.
Text.LocalizedString: We're married now, <PlayerName>$Player</>...I'm your wife.

Text.SourceString: You know, everyone in town always tells me how lucky I am to have you as my partner.
Text.LocalizedString: You know, everyone in town always tells me how lucky I am to have you as my partner.

Text.SourceString: Surprise! I baked these cookies just for you.//I thought they would be the perfect treat to sweeten your day. Enjoy!
Text.LocalizedString: Surprise! I baked these cookies just for you.//I thought they would be the perfect treat to sweeten your day. Enjoy!

Text.SourceString: Look what I made for you! I put a lot of love into them.//I hope you enjoy this little homemade treat.
Text.LocalizedString: Look what I made for you! I put a lot of love into them.//I hope you enjoy this little homemade treat.
